# EmailJS config for sending "forgot password" verification codes.
# Without these set, the app runs in demo mode: the reset code is shown
# directly on screen instead of being emailed, so you can still test the
# whole flow before setting this up.
#
# 1. Create a free account at https://www.emailjs.com
# 2. Add an Email Service (e.g. connect your Gmail) — copy its Service ID
# 3. Create an Email Template using these variables in the body:
#      {{to_email}}  {{to_name}}  {{code}}
#    e.g. "Hi {{to_name}}, your Habit Tracker password reset code is {{code}}."
#    Copy its Template ID.
# 4. Find your Public Key under Account -> General.
# 5. Fill these in below, rename this file to .env, restart `npm run dev`.
VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=your-service-id
VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=your-template-id
VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=your-public-key
